Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

While potatoes cook, trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Roast on middle rack until lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and dice @Apple{1}(halved, cored and diced) into 1⁄4-inch pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Pat @Beef Tenderloin Filets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @Brown Sugar Bourbon Seasoning{10.8%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add beef and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If beef begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

Turn off heat; transfer beef to a #plate{}. Wipe out #pan{}.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef. Cook chicken until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per side, or cook pork to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

Heat @Butter{2%tablespoon} (3 TBSP for 4 servings) and a drizzle of oil in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add apple and scallion whites; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup}, and @Sugar{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp for 4). Cook until sauce has thickened and apple is tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

In the last 2 minutes of cooking, return beef to pan until warmed through. Season with salt and pepper. Turn off heat.

> Swap in chicken or pork for beef.

Mash potatoes with a #potato masher{} until mostly smooth.

Stir in scallion greens, @Sour Cream{1.5%tablespoon}, @Butter{1%TBSP}, and a splash of reserved potato cooking liquid. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered until ready to serve.

> TIP: If needed, add more reserved potato cooking liquid a splash at a time until potatoes are smooth and creamy.

Divide beef, mashed potatoes, and Brussels sprouts between plates. Top beef with apple pan sauce and serve.